1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:03,480
Now once we have the Demo GPT model defined,

2

00:00:03,480  -->  00:00:05,920
let's talk about how to train it.

3

00:00:05,920  -->  00:00:09,460
It will be very similar to training other models.

4

00:00:09,460  -->  00:00:12,320
On every iteration, using a data loader,

5

00:00:12,320  -->  00:00:15,680
we will load a batch of inputs and targets,

6

00:00:15,680  -->  00:00:21,180
and both inputs and targets will be tensors with token IDs.

7

00:00:21,180  -->  00:00:24,460
We will then pass a batch of inputs to the model,

8

00:00:24,460  -->  00:00:26,860
and it will return its predictions.

9

00:00:26,860  -->  00:00:29,000
We'll use these predictions and use

10

00:00:29,000  -->  00:00:32,925
the expected targets to calculate the loss for this batch.

11

00:00:32,925  -->  00:00:34,940
Have any loss for a single batch,

12

00:00:34,940  -->  00:00:37,180
we can calculate the gradients.

13

00:00:37,180  -->  00:00:39,510
Using the optimizer instance,

14

00:00:39,510  -->  00:00:42,760
we will update parameters of our model.

15

00:00:42,760  -->  00:00:46,570
This is a single iteration for training our model.

16

00:00:46,570  -->  00:00:52,110
We can now repeat this again and again using different batches of data.
